Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.50,0:00:04.46,SignA,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten years ago, somewhere in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.79,0:00:21.33,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.34,0:00:25.00,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.38,0:00:28.78,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Just sing, like you always do.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.78,0:00:31.76,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I love your songs, Setsuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.65,0:00:34.47,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Container shields deployed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.29,0:00:39.22,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let me hear you sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.27,0:00:50.44,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.43,0:00:53.11,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The moment she started singing,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.11,0:00:57.21,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,the brain wave electromagnetic resonance \Nspectrum intensity increased by twelve digits!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.00,0:01:05.50,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,High-density libido is materializing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.25,0:01:08.30,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Activating Orgone charger.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.33,0:01:19.30,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This is the next generation of energy!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.06,0:01:21.97,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.79,0:03:05.35,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Lappa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.00,0:03:08.48,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Setsuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.18,0:03:12.37,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Mao-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.78,0:03:15.84,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The hibiscus is blooming beautifully.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.94,0:03:18.71,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's so brilliantly colored.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:21.24,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.05,0:03:26.18,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(735,1)}Through the Window of Setsuna
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.21,0:03:33.56,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's the Vice Commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.56,0:03:35.19,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Said she had something to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.19,0:03:38.64,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.82,0:03:44.62,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're the captain, so you \Ncan't rely on Rita-san forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.13,0:03:46.74,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.73,0:03:49.53,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Last time, it was my fault the enemy escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.83,0:03:51.83,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.07,0:03:55.55,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You saved us last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:04:00.92,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the Nebula Engine's testing wasn't done yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.69,0:04:02.80,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You surprised me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.34,0:04:05.56,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It was like what happened with the Earth Engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.98,0:04:11.11,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But if this'll make you feel better, \NI'll take it, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:14.69,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Two more to go...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.69,0:04:16.15,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.70,0:04:19.81,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,One of them is Siren-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.81,0:04:21.11,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,"Sama"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:23.76,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know their avatar name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.35,0:04:26.03,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What does Pitz say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.03,0:04:30.53,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The image isn't as clear as last time...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.53,0:04:34.50,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But he says he can sense Orgone energy moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.97,0:04:37.46,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What's Rita-san doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.46,0:04:40.56,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she went to get some good food...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.56,0:04:42.24,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.79,0:04:43.97,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That is possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.62,0:04:47.34,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't think so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.32,0:04:56.29,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.29,0:04:56.94,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.83,0:04:59.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.43,0:05:06.06,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,From your voice, I guessed you were pretty,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.57,0:05:08.17,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,but you're prettier than I imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.23,0:05:13.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's still early, but do you \Nwant something to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.83,0:05:16.92,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A bourbon on the rocks, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.43,0:05:26.40,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,So what do you want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.40,0:05:28.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You used to be a detective with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.38,0:05:31.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But you quit ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.05,0:05:35.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell me why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.73,0:05:39.19,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Women like you scare me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.65,0:05:44.28,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,If they think they have a reason, \Nthey'll tell any lie straight-faced.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.43,0:05:47.57,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Between being a detective and a bartender,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.57,0:05:52.87,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I've gotten pretty good at guessing \Nwhat someone does for a living.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.69,0:05:55.48,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,A journalist, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:05:57.91,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.91,0:06:01.34,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, you're interested in \Nthe Kanda incident, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.34,0:06:02.34,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.77,0:06:06.64,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I was on the task force for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.64,0:06:09.92,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,But the official story is that the case was solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.92,0:06:11.39,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.91,0:06:13.60,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Everything you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.60,0:06:15.31,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Everything you remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.05,0:06:21.06,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything beyond \Nwhat was in the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.67,0:06:25.78,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Then, your thoughts regarding the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.14,0:06:29.00,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,That's a very abstract way of putting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.09,0:06:32.81,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, Macbeth Enterprises was developing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.81,0:06:37.25,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,a man-machine interface for new mobile weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.61,0:06:39.31,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,To aid in their research,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.31,0:06:44.21,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,they had six children, believed to have been \Ncreated by illegal genetic manipulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.28,0:06:51.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,An anonymous whistleblower \Nreported them to the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.93,0:06:53.99,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,and Macbeth was investigated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.37,0:06:58.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The six children were found \Nand taken by the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.77,0:07:01.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Children born in Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.46,0:07:03.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,but who didn't appear in any government records...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.49,0:07:09.28,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Macbeth was using those children \Nto develop weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.07,0:07:12.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, this was a major human rights violation,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.81,0:07:15.33,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,and the responsible parties were arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.93,0:07:19.09,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, there were cases \Noccurring in the Tokyo suburbs
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.09,0:07:21.70,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,where people would fall into \Na comatose state at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.70,0:07:24.44,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,and not wake up for several days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.04,0:07:28.43,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,It was said that a Macbeth \Nexperiment caused that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.71,0:07:36.08,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,After that, there was a purging \Nat Macbeth's executive level,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.08,0:07:39.71,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,and supposedly, the majority of \Ntheir operations were reformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.38,0:07:42.59,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.59,0:07:47.57,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,members of the Kube family, the original \Nfounders, were the next executives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.08,0:07:51.65,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Kube took advantage of the \Nincident to return to power.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.62,0:07:56.12,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, the incident was \Nblamed on Takashi Kanda,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.12,0:07:59.62,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,the former CEO who had \Ntaken over Macbeth previously.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.18,0:08:01.58,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.19,0:08:07.00,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Kanda committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.69,0:08:14.30,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you quit the force?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.46,0:08:20.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to those six children?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.34,0:08:23.23,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.40,0:08:27.21,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what you wanted to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.99,0:08:33.29,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Akari... Is it okay for us to have fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.71,0:08:36.20,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The motto of the Midsummer's Knights
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:38.83,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,is to do what you have to, when you have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.83,0:08:40.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of the time, we're free.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.23,0:08:43.71,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Did Daichi decide that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.71,0:08:46.25,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,No, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.87,0:08:49.84,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You came all the way here. \NAren't you going to swim?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.19,0:08:52.80,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Only children come to the pool to swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.80,0:08:55.52,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Then what did you come here to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.52,0:09:00.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Relax and enjoy all the guys looking at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.01,0:09:00.94,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.94,0:09:03.02,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm jealous of the squirrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.35,0:09:08.10,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was a bad idea to bring Hana.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.65,0:09:09.94,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Akari...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.60,0:09:13.03,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,She's been swimming this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.45,0:09:18.12,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what really happened to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.12,0:09:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were there any photos?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.00,0:09:23.70,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,No, I heard all our materials on \Nthem were destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.42,0:09:28.84,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,I was on the task force,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.84,0:09:32.05,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,and even I don't know where they went afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.94,0:09:34.57,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,All we were told was that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.57,0:09:39.76,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,to protect their rights, measures were taken to \Nkeep their personal information confidential.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.15,0:09:44.05,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,So I looked into it myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.05,0:09:46.35,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,and they found out, and fired me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.76,0:09:49.06,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you decide to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.06,0:09:51.02,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Something wasn't right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.86,0:09:52.69,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.29,0:09:56.57,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Were those children really being kept safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.07,0:09:59.08,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have any proof,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.08,0:10:01.53,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,but it didn't seem that way to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.89,0:10:03.36,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.80,0:10:05.04,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.64,0:10:11.10,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to them after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.67,0:10:13.95,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.97,0:10:18.55,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to ask the guys who fired me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.53,0:10:20.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.95,0:10:23.10,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And thanks for the drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.70,0:10:27.05,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where they went?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.37,0:10:33.57,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,As you said, the government \Nhad no records on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.57,0:10:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but they had names inside the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.18,0:10:40.24,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,And they had numbers, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.06,0:10:47.00,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Each of them had a serial number \Nbetween three and eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.12,0:10:53.15,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Which means there was also a one and two.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.15,0:10:55.16,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe there were even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.84,0:11:01.73,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Are they still involved in some kind \Nof illegal weapons development?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.69,0:11:05.28,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, I think they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.83,0:11:08.77,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Takashi Kanda committed suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.52,0:11:12.52,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,and I inherited this company and you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.75,0:11:24.85,Default - flashback,G,0000,0000,0000,,This is Kube, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.89,0:11:28.20,Default - flashback,K,0000,0000,0000,,Kanda-san, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.79,0:11:30.97,Default - flashback,G,0000,0000,0000,,I've been set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.97,0:11:32.57,Default - flashback,G,0000,0000,0000,,But not by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.03,0:11:34.46,Default - flashback,G,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.93,0:11:40.26,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I think that our meeting was
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.26,0:11:44.64,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,a very fortunate event for both parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.01,0:11:47.92,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,You "think," eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.80,0:11:52.27,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Puck, could you kill someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.70,0:11:56.11,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you ever think you want to kill someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.90,0:11:59.08,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,There is a high probability
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.08,0:12:02.78,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,that the weapons I devise will be used \Nto take lives on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.78,0:12:07.96,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,In that sense, it is true that \NI am a party to murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.96,0:12:13.35,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,But I have never thought about \Nkilling a specific individual,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.35,0:12:15.75,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,nor would I do such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.95,0:12:28.59,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Takashi Kanda has committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.86,0:12:36.48,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,My sole reason for existing is to do my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.42,0:12:39.53,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Puck does not lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.89,0:12:47.62,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.37,0:12:50.38,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,And we're running out of capsules, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.38,0:12:52.24,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.83,0:12:56.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,If Siren-sama awakens, we'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.29,0:13:00.05,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We can make new capsules.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.87,0:13:04.51,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Is the seat next to you free?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.85,0:13:05.96,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.42,0:13:07.89,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.75,0:13:17.23,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Want some?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.82,0:13:20.07,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.07,0:13:24.16,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What a kind offer to a girl \Nyou've just met. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.16,0:13:25.57,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You were swimming a lot, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.71,0:13:29.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,My quota is 1,200 meters a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.20,0:13:32.43,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Are you on the swim team or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.43,0:13:35.00,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.36,0:13:40.69,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But I've been told to exercise, \Nso I can stay healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.69,0:13:43.66,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's a good thing, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.66,0:13:44.94,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.94,0:13:48.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad they gave me such kind advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.47,0:13:51.26,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I could never do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.06,0:13:55.39,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Two squirrels?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.79,0:13:57.77,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Did you make a friend, Pitz?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:02.61,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Lappa is my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.61,0:14:03.62,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.55,0:14:07.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Does that squirrel talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.54,0:14:10.80,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Squirrels don't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.42,0:14:12.97,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.74,0:14:17.92,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,How can I be the heroine, when I'm \Nthe only one without a squirrel?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:20.38,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,This whole thing is squirrely!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.32,0:14:24.34,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The project's finally nearing its final stages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.80,0:14:26.84,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This install device
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.84,0:14:31.18,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,seems to be a system to give \Nthe subject a specific dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.18,0:14:33.93,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Why does it come in pairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.25,0:14:36.30,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Ban-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.30,0:14:40.88,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take care of the rest myself. \NYou can go home for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.66,0:14:45.39,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,My contract with my sponsor means
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.39,0:14:47.87,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,that I can't show anyone the tests, even you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.05,0:14:51.28,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, did that upset you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.67,0:14:59.16,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm your assistant, so of course \NI'll do whatever you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.72,0:15:00.50,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.29,0:15:04.92,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do it all on your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.75,0:15:07.40,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.22,0:15:11.90,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it be convenient if there \Nwere another one of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.10,0:15:20.74,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.01,0:15:23.71,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Setsuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.84,0:15:27.21,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.21,0:15:29.61,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's still blooming beautifully.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.09,0:15:31.71,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.71,0:15:37.84,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But it seems to me you like sitting by \Nthe window more than you like the plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.84,0:15:39.62,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:41.89,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're amazing, Mao-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.89,0:15:44.08,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You know everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.77,0:15:49.67,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,A long time ago, I wasn't allowed \Nto go outside when I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.09,0:15:54.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I can do that now, so I'm really happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.92,0:15:58.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I can visit it whenever I want, \Nthe world I see outside the window
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.24,0:16:03.18,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,looks totally different than it used to. \NIt makes me happy to see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.94,0:16:05.21,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Setsuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:09.99,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Time for your medical checkup.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.50,0:16:16.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sick, so why do you give \Nme so many examinations?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.05,0:16:20.75,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're that important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.49,0:16:24.44,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,So sit in that machine today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.78,0:16:28.91,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,A medical equipment manufacturer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.91,0:16:31.07,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Akari did some research,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.07,0:16:35.26,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,and found that this research group was \Nconnected with Macbeth Enterprises.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.94,0:16:38.47,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's probably something here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.20,0:16:47.90,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.90,0:16:48.90,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Good to see both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.02,0:16:50.90,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.88,0:17:08.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Amarok and Malkin...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.54,0:17:11.47,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We can assume they're the enemy leaders, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.14,0:17:13.21,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.06,0:17:17.65,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But since they have avatar bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.65,0:17:20.86,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,they must have thought of themselves \Nas being from Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.86,0:17:23.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,until they awakened as Planetary Gears.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.73,0:17:27.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,When did they awaken?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.11,0:17:33.19,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,If you kiss, you can read someone's \Nmind for a second, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.54,0:17:39.88,Default - flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,I think we have special powers \Nbecause we're designer children.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.88,0:17:42.12,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,Is that why they lock us up?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.53,0:17:45.41,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,And why we can only see the \Noutside from the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.08,0:17:51.35,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Amara... Moco.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.35,0:17:52.79,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.79,0:17:55.22,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You get to leave this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.22,0:17:57.37,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to a country called Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.13,0:18:00.14,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.47,0:18:05.10,Default - flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,What is this device?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.10,0:18:06.96,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This is your machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.64,0:18:11.90,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's a Neural Maneuver System \Ncreated specifically for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.56,0:18:14.08,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.38,0:18:43.50,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You think one of their friends is here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.50,0:18:46.18,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Probably. They likely haven't awakened, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.88,0:18:49.62,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You said that touching a powerful Orgone energy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.62,0:18:53.69,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,or kissing an awakened avatar brings \Nback their memories, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.17,0:18:54.86,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.35,0:18:57.79,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And even if an avatar hasn't awakened,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.79,0:19:02.32,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,if they kiss you, they can read your mind \Nor telepathically communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.48,0:19:15.34,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,My beautiful Setsuna...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.40,0:19:19.34,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You're so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.14,0:19:26.60,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if the designer children
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.60,0:19:30.81,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,weren't created as pilots for new weapons,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.81,0:19:35.94,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,but as vessels to install a human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.62,0:19:41.80,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, if you could keep installing \Nyour mind into a young body,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.80,0:19:44.04,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,you could become immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.47,0:19:53.12,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.90,0:19:55.88,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.88,0:19:57.17,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.67,0:20:01.66,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You were raising me to be your own vessel!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.66,0:20:03.13,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're a terrible person!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.13,0:20:04.51,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Setsuna!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.95,0:20:06.85,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.33,0:20:38.12,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, behind you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.71,0:20:39.63,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi Manatsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.99,0:20:43.48,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You drove Albion mad, so we'll kill you first!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.13,0:20:54.48,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,This light...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.35,0:20:58.90,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.31,0:21:00.71,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The Livlaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.51,0:21:07.03,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Albion was the other Neoteny that \NLieban was talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.54,0:21:15.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Albion is a Neoteny?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.88,0:21:19.46,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.09,0:21:41.23,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,They did a good job of cleaning it up, \Nbut someone just shed blood here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.67,0:21:42.65,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.38,0:21:47.49,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But it isn't Siren-sama's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.74,0:21:59.90,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.56,0:22:02.17,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the install device?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.72,0:22:04.39,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,It's been safely removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.97,0:22:07.88,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Then take it to the place I directed you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.58,0:22:12.10,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Understood, Robin-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.48,0:22:19.96,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Siren-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.75,0:22:23.66,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,She wasn't on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.61,0:22:27.98,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,This keeps getting more complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.09,0:22:34.50,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Amara.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.27,0:22:35.91,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.24,0:24:16.22,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Every night, illegal fighting matches
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.22,0:24:19.35,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,are held at an underground ring in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.35,0:24:23.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, bets are placed on the fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.01,0:24:27.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,And the next Machine Goodfellow \Nis going to appear in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.71,0:24:32.15,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Is the enemy one of the boys \Nthat are forced to fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.15,0:24:34.95,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, on episode 12 of {\i1}Captain Earth{\i0}:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:36.87,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Boys' Battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:36.87,Title2,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Boys' Battlefield
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.87,0:24:39.56,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine, scramble!
